'''溴化钇'''是一种无机化合物，化学式为YBr<sub>3</sub>，为白色固体。无水溴化钇可由[[氧化钇|氧化钇]]或溴化钇的水合物与[[溴化铵|溴化铵]]反应，经(NH<sub>4</sub>)<sub>3</sub>YBr<sub>6</sub>中间体得到。<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Journal of the Less Common Metals|volume=127|language=en|date=1987-01|pages=155–160|doi=10.1016/0022-5088(87)90372-9|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0022508887903729|title=The ammonium-bromide route to anhydrous rare earth bromides MBr3|accessdate=2020-07-04|author=Gerd Meyer, Siegfried Dötsch, Thomas Staffel|archive-date=2020-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200825114804/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0022508887903729|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[碳化钇|碳化钇]]（YC<sub>2</sub>）和溴反应，也能制得溴化钇。<ref>Mussler, R. E.; Campbell, T. T.; Block, F. E.; Robidart, G. B. Metallothermic reduction of yttrium halides. ''Bureau of Mines Report of Investigations'', 1963. 6259. pp 21.</ref>它可以被金属钇还原为低价态的YBr或Y<sub>2</sub>Br<sub>3</sub><ref>{{cite journal|journal=Inorganic Chemistry|volume=19|issue=7|language=en|issn=0020-1669|date=1980-07|pages=2128–2132|doi=10.1021/ic50209a057|url=https://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/ic50209a057|title=Reduced halides of yttrium with strong metal-metal bonding: yttrium monochloride, monobromide, sesquichloride, and sesquibromide|accessdate=2020-07-04|author=H. Mattausch, J. B. Hendricks, R. Eger, J. D. Corbett, A. Simon|archive-date=2020-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200705212952/https://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/ic50209a057|dead-url=no}}</ref>；溴化钇、钇和[[锇|锇]]共同反应，可以生成Y<sub>4</sub>Br<sub>4</sub>Os<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Journal of the American Chemical Society|volume=114|issue=5|language=en|issn=0002-7863|date=1992-02|pages=1697–1701|doi=10.1021/ja00031a024|url=https://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/ja00031a024|title=A novel structure type in reduced rare-earth metal halides. One-dimensional confacial chains based on centered square antiprismatic metal units: Y4Br4Os and Er4Br4Os|accessdate=2020-07-04|author=Peter K. Dorhout, John D. Corbett|archive-date=2020-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200705145845/https://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/ja00031a024|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

